rows.content:
I purchased my Samsung Galaxy S22 in 2023, trusting Samsung’s reputation for high-quality, reliable devices. However, after a recent software update, vertical lines started appearing on my display. Initially, there was just one line, but now there are three. The service center confirmed it’s a display issue, and since my device is out of warranty, I’ve been quoted approximately INR 11,000 for a replacement._x000d_
_x000d_
What’s especially disappointing is that Samsung offers free display replacements for the S22 Ultra, but not for the S22, despite the fact that my issue arose after a software update. This feels unfair, particularly for a premium model like the Galaxy S22. I find this situation frustrating and unexpected. Some of my friends are also facing the same issue with their Samsung Galaxy S22 devices._x000d_
_x000d_
It’s also disheartening to compare this experience with competitors like Apple and OnePlus, who offer post-warranty display replacements for similar issues._x000d_
rows.AI Insight: The user is experiencing vertical lines appearing on the display of their Samsung Galaxy S22 after a software update, which has worsened from one line to three lines. The issue is confirmed by a service center as a display defect, and the user expresses frustration that Samsung does not offer free replacement for this issue despite it occurring after a software update and despite the device being a premium model.

Dear Samsung,_x000d_
_x000d_
I am writing to you because of an issue that has emerged last night on its own. A pink vertical line has appeared on the display screen of my Samsung Galaxy M 52 5G yesterday night. After researching a bit, I found that I am not the first and only one who has faced this issue. This is happening for the past 2 years with multiple users of Samsung Galaxy M Series and S Series. It is happening because of faulty monthly security patches that had been releasing for the past 2 years. I was fortunate enough to have faced this issue at a later stage but was unfortunate to know that the cause of this is sourced at Samsung only. I must tell you that most of us has perfectly working devices with no scratches on the display screen or on any place on our phones. It does not look good on the brand value of Samsung that you are not even accepting this issue which is happening on such a large scale around the globe, causing serious damages in terms of screen replacement cost. Help me._x000d_

rows.content:
Touchscreen Freeze Issue on Samsung Galaxy F14 5G After 1 November 2024 Update_x000d_
_x000d_
Problem Summary:_x000d_
After updating to the 1 November 2024 security patch on 4 January 2025, my phone's touchscreen started freezing. The touch worked for about 1 minute after every reboot but stopped responding completely after that._x000d_
_x000d_
Steps Taken:_x000d_
_x000d_
1. Rebooted the phone using Power + Volume Down. Touch worked briefly but froze again._x000d_
_x000d_
_x000d_
2. Checked Double Tap to Wake—it worked, suggesting hardware was intact._x000d_
_x000d_
_x000d_
3. Used an OTG mouse to reset all settings, but the issue persisted._x000d_
_x000d_
_x000d_
4. Performed a factory reset, which resolved the issue._x000d_
_x000d_
_x000d_
_x000d_
Possible Cause:_x000d_
The problem likely stemmed from a bug in the update, causing a software glitch or corrupted firmware._x000d_
_x000d_
Resolution:_x000d_
A factory reset fixed the issue, and the touchscreen is now functioning normally._x000d_
_x000d_
Suggestion:_x000d_
Please investigate the 1 November 2024 update for potential touchscreen-related bugs and release a patch if necessary._x000d_
rows.AI Insight: The touchscreen on the Samsung Galaxy F14 5G froze after the November 1, 2024 software update, functioning only briefly after each reboot before stopping completely, and the issue was resolved only by a factory reset.
